            <PivotItem Header="Welcome to Mahjong!">
                <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
                    <StackPanel MaxWidth="460">
                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,10">
                            Mahjong is a 4-player game that originated in China, but has since spread to Japan, America, and many other countries. 
                            One of the things I love about Mahjong is that everyone plays differently. 
                            The rules vary greatly from country to country, region to region, even family to family.
                        </TextBlock>
                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,0,0,10"> 
                            Even without the rule variations, Mahjong's rules can be a bit complicated. 
                            This app is meant to help with that. 
                            It calculates scores for each round, keeps track of everyone's scores, and hopefully teaches you how to play the game. 
                            The app uses custom Mahjong rules that my family has used for a long time. 
                            They're based on a book from the 1960s called A Mahjong Handbook, similar to standard Japanese Mahjong Rules circa 1965. 
                            But like most Mahjong rule sets, it's evolved in our family over the years. 
                            They're fun, and I've done my best to document them here. 
                            I've also tried to make this app flexible enough to accommodate rule variations.
                        </TextBlock>

                        <TextBlock TextWrapping="WrapWholeWords" Margin="0,0,0,10">
                            Swipe over to learn more about how to play this version of Mahjong, and how to use this app to keep track of games and calculate scores.
                        </TextBlock>
                    </StackPanel>
                </ScrollViewer>
            </PivotItem> 
            
            
            
